The paper deals with a coordination problem in distributed computing, specifically in a system of agents with limited memory and communication. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) category. The problem involves maintaining a stable population size in the presence of an adversary, which could fall under the Game Theory (cs.GT) or Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) categories. The paper also presents a protocol that uses a novel coloring strategy, which could relate to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) or Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories.
